## Commit conventions (LSI)

Follow **Conventional Commits**: `type(scope): imperative subject` — ≤ ~72 chars, no trailing period.

- **One logical change per commit** — do not mix unrelated feature, refactor, and fix.
- **Commit plan first** when multiple logical changes exist (see `.lsi/workflows/commits-logical-order.md`).
- **Only run `git commit` when the user explicitly asks.**

Full spec: `.lsi/workflows/commits-logical-order.md`
